<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-08-27T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-08-27T22:00:00-05:00" n="125" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d125">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">811.248/686: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-27T23:00:00-04:00">August 27,
                                1942—11 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>775. Your 936, August 13, 1 p.m. The Department has found your telegram under
                        reference most helpful. The Department transmitted the substance to the War
                        Department and the War Department has stated that the views expressed by you
                        in regard to the potentialities of an American air force in China coincide
                        with the views held by that Department.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>